members.biography:
Khalil Alami is the founder and CEO of the leading online payment gateway company Telr and has

more than 23 years of proven leadership experience within the financial services, fintech, as well

as the payments and card industries across the United States, UAE, Jordan, and Saudi Arabia.

 

Under Khalil's leadership, Telr has achieved numerous accolades, including being listed among

Forbes Middle East Fintech 50 2024, Fintech Company of the Year 2024 by Finance Middle East

Awards 2024, Best Payment Gateway of the Year 2024' for both the UAE and Saudi Arabia by

Global Business and Finance Magazine, Middle East, Forbes Top 30 Fintech Companies in 2023,

winning the "Payment Gateway of the Year Award" by Entrepreneur Middle East, and winning the

Car24 Outliers Challenge by Hub71 Outliers Challenge.

 

Khalil himself has been recognized as one of the Top 20 Performing CEOs in the MENA region by

Unlock Media.

A well-acknowledged and globally respected industry expert, a startup mentor, and an advocate

for financial education, Khalil has built multiple multi-million-dollar organizations by leveraging indepth

knowledge on international payments architecture, card processing and settlement, network

security, the four-party system, as well as electronic and mobile payments.

 

He is also a member of the Arab Monetary Fund’s (AMF) Regional Fintech Working Group, and

previously was a board member of the Young Entrepreneurs Association (YEA) in Jordan.

As the founder and CEO of Telr, Khalil Alami has built up the talent, operations, processes, and

tech at the company, following which he closed a $15 million funding round to grow the company

into one of the Top 3 online payment gateways in the UAE and Saudi Arabia. Through Telr, Khalil has

enabled merchants - including startups, SMEs, government bodies, and large corporates - to

accept payments online through a proprietary, highly customizable, and extremely secure

payment gateway offering.

 

He is passionate about personalizing and customizing customer experiences; paying attention to

how merchants are onboarded; making pricing structures viable; strengthening consumer

touchpoints across e-commerce and social commerce; as well as maintaining people’s safety and

security across all financial services transactions.

 

Khalil has an MBA degree from the American University of Beirut as well as a bachelor’s degree in

economics, MIS, political science, and management from Purdue University.

members.biography:
Besides managing the family business in the pharmaceutical field, Ashraf has started, managed, and consulted several businesses in the fields of design, advertising, and media marketing. In 2011, he followed his passion for social entrepreneurship by accepting the challenge to join a global NGO as their Middle East Director. He also acts as a consultant and mentor to several startups with Health 2.0 and the African Entrepreneurship Award.

In more recent years, Ashraf has merged his passion and expertise in tech-entrepreneurship and health, through the highly innovative and trailblazing venture that is O7 Therapy. Alongside the highly-esteemed psychiatrist, founder of Nine Psychology, Dr. Ashraf Adel, and entrepreneurial technology expert and founder of EME International, Nader Iskander, Ashraf has developed O7 Therapy from the ground-up.

Ashraf believes that the impact of technological enhancement can be the driving force behind the success of industries across the board. He recognizes the potential technology has, and is unwilling to settle on professionalism and user-experience, especially when it comes to the journey to mental health and wellness. For Ashraf, the building of O7 Therapy is living proof that technology has the capacity to bridge the gaps in holistic health care by reaching its full value, through accessibility and excellence.

O7 Therapy is an online platform and curated network of hand-picked Arabic-speaking psychiatrists and psychotherapists, as well as a referral network of specialized clinics and hospitals to support people struggling with mental health challenges in the MENA region. Founded on the conviction that every individual deserves the opportunity to pursue mental wellness and healing, together the O7 Founders have built a refined, scientific, and research-based online platform, established to support an ongoing journey to mental wellness. The platform provides top-notch online psychotherapy and ensures security and safety, using trusted protocols for data-encryption and storage, within a user-friendly framework. Still fresh on the ground, O7 Therapy has revolutionized the definition of online therapeutic support, and is providing polished, collaborative, and meaningful mental health services for Arabic-speaking people worldwide.

Ashraf graduated from the German school in Cairo, holds a B.Sc. in Pharmaceutical Sciences from Cairo University, and a MSc. in Technology Entrepreneurship from University of Maryland. Additionally, he studied Integrated Marketing Communications at the Chartered Institute of Marketing, UK.
